{meta: title Calm The Storm}
{meta: artist Doyle Lawson}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Come and calm this raging storm
The storm for me (calm the storm for me)
Roll the [F]clouds (roll those heavy storm clouds)
Out of the [C]way (all the clouds away)
Make me see (see the light that's shining)
The blessed [Am]light (see the blessed lighthouse)
When you [C]calm (when you calm)
The [G7]storm for [C]me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
All my life I've heard the story
About a [F]man from Gali[C]lee
How He calmed the raging river
And He [D7]walked the stormy [G7]sea (walked the stormy sea)
I can [C]feel the winds a-blowing
Here [F]upon my bended [C]knees
So I'm callin' out to you Lord
[G7]Come and calm the sea for [C]me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
